caption.text:
[MY DIARY : August, 27th 2017]
I can say that two days ago was my special day! 
But I wish everyday will be special.. hahahaa 
Two days ago, I celebrated my birthday with my new Japanese friends. I just have known them two days before my birthday. Because I knew that no one could celebrate my birthday (oh, so pity), I decided to celebrate it with them as they would leave Jogja the day after my birthday. They were so cute and so interesting. Glad to meet them and celebrate my birthday with them! 
Then, yesterday, I ate out with (also) my new Japanese friend. She is 3 years older than me. We talked about many things. I found that she is so interesting!! ... and TODAY ...
I ate out with my sister. She bought me tart cake!! I was really happy!! My sister is the best 😄
(The best part of today)
Because I didn't wanna eat cake by myself, I brought it to the place which is called 'gelanggang mahasiswa ugm' ..ermm... gelanggang, again, and again ... There, my friends and I ate my birthday cake!
That moment was quite strange, but I was really really happy! 
My gelanggang friends (let me call them my gelanggang friends ya), sang 'happy birthday' to me and...I was so happy that I couldn't say it by words... I was speechless.. the best lah!! They made me cry successfully... Glad to know them all... They are truly my new family ☺
Thanks' GOD! 
Glad to be 20 years old..

caption.text:
July, 16th 2017 (ten days ago) "The second time to be there"
I'm Balinese but there are many things that I still don't know about Bali. I want to know more about Bali (especially the tourism spots, haha). That's why I decided to explore Bali on my holiday. 
I love traveling, but rarely I go to tourism place by my self. 😅

I had had a plan to go to some popular temples for holy-holiday. I really wanted to go to Besakih Temple or Lempuyang Temple. Accidentally, one of my high-school best friend asked me to go to Karangasem regency (East-Bali). It was about 2.5 hours from my hometown, Singaraja (North-Bali). On the way to go there, we stopped at two popular temples called Ponjok Batu Temple and Lempuyang Temple and prayed for a while there. 🙏
Next holiday I'll go to Besakih temple!! Then we continued our journey to 'Taman Ujung' the popular tourism spot which is used to be 'Bali Palace'. It was the second time for me to go there. I do really love this place. Someday I want to go there with you! 😍😍😍 After taking lots of pictures, we went eating on the sea-side 'warung' near the palace. Then we visited 'Chocolate Factory' and ate some bars of chocolate (quite expensive for us but tasted perfect). After that, we backed to Singaraja. On the way to home, sometimes we stopped somewhere and took a lot of pictures, again and again. 
Bali is so awesome! ...Sorry for my grammar ya!

#bali #tamanujung

caption.text:
[Yesterday]
My best friend and I went to restaurant which is located in Lovina Bali called 'Lovina Life'. The place was quite good. 
But let's talk about my best girl friend! 
Fo me, the girl who took this photo is so special because she is my first best friend. 
Erm... We are best friend since 2007 (at that time we were about 10 years old). Thank you for being my best friend yaa~ 
I'm so glad that I've a lot of best friends now, but still, she is the first one. 
Even when we meet each other, we'll talk a lot. Yesterday, we talked about many things like our problems (especially hers), our campus life, my good-looking boy friends (please ignore this, haha) and more. 
When she started to talk about her problems, I was really confused because I didn't know how to amuse her. I just listened to her and supported her just by saying "Don't worry, you can bear it, just stay strong!" But we know that 'saying' is so easier rather than 'doing', right? 
Oh, It's so hard but she still looks so happy like nothing happened. I'm so sure that she can take it in hand. 
I do have my own problems. I've ever had problems. I was so sad and so suppressed by those problems. But listening to hers, I feel that I'm luckier than her. So that, I have to be more cheerful than her. ＼(^▽^)／
Be strong! We gonna be alright! (・∇・) #bestfriend #lovina #bali

[2 days ago] [5 hours after arriving in Bali] 
I went to my best friend house. 
Then I took photos with her, and also her sisters. 
I really like this photo so I decided to share it here. 
What did they do?
Have you ever heard 'mesangih' or 'mepandes' before? 
It's teeth-cutting Hinduism ritual, as a symbol of being adult. Of course, just once a life. The people who have done this hoped to be able to control themselves from six enemies inside human being called 'sad ripu' in particular much better. The 'sad ripu' consisted of: lust, greed, anger, arrogance, attachment, and covetousness. 
This ceremony is a symbol!
I do think that every ceremony is important. But, we have to remember that interpreting the ceremony, then trying to control ourselves, thinking positively, and doing good things are also important (may be much more important). I think most of my friends are good at it. 
I did 'mepandes' ceremony 4 years ago. Since then, I've been trying to control myself, not only from 'sad ripu', but also from a lot of things. It is because I wanna be better person who can be useful to others, and I'm still trying for that. ..keep trying... ☺

By the way, I'm still studying English, so forgive me for my grammar. 
#hinduism #hindu #bali #balinese #mepandes #mesangih #metatah #balinesegirls

caption.text:
Social Project : Bersih-Bersih oleh Cofas Kelompok 4 Vokasi Barat "Keep it green, keep it clean and enjoy its beauty." -source : google

Akhirnya kegiatan social project kami berjalan dengan lancar. Kami telah membersihkan alun-alun utara Jogja dan daerah di sekitarnya pada tanggal 22 Juni 2016 dari pukul 16.30-18.45 WIB. 
Kami tidak hanya membersihkan lingkungan, namun juga membagikan stiker yang bertuliskan "Bersihkan Tempat, Luruskan Niat", dengan maksud untuk ikut menyadarkan masyarakat akan pentingnya menjaga kebersihan. 
Tentu ada banyak manfaat yang kami peroleh dari kegiatan ini. Selain dapat membersihkan lingkungan dan menyadarkan masyarakat, hubungan kami satu sama lain juga menjadi semakin erat karena kami bekerja bersama-sama. 
Secara tidak sadar, kami telah mengimplementasikan ketiga konsep 'Tri Hita Karana' : 
1. Menjaga hubungan baik antara manusia dengan Tuhan. Di bulan suci ini teman-teman saya berbuka puasa bersama dan kemudian beribadah bersama. Saya juga menyempatkan diri untuk pergi sembahyang seusai berkegiatan. 
2. Menjaga hubungan baik antara manusia dengan manusia. Kami tidak mungkin saling mengenal tanpa adanya kegiatan ini. Sungguh merupakan kegiatan yang bermanfaat yang bahkan dapat menambah relasi pertemanan. 
3. Menjaga hubungan baik antara manusia dengan LINGKUNGAN. Kami senang dapat membersihkan lingkungan bersama-sama sehingga pekerjaan cepat terselesaikan. 
Semoga kegiatan kami dapat menginspirasi banyak orang... :) #PALAPAPeduli
